{
  "text": "Myopia, especially high myopia (<-6.0 D), is a highly prevalent, complex ocular phenotype and public health problem worldwide [CITATION_1] . Some etiological studies show that genetic factors play an important role in the development of high myopia [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Some genes have been identified as candidate genes of high myopia [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] , although it is still uncertain which genes are specifically responsible for myopia.",
  "correct_citation": {
